Crystal bells found throughout Eorzea can be used to summon an aesthetician.
Private chambers can now be added to free company estates.
Members with personal chambers can now be discharged from free companies. Any items kept within the chambers can be reclaimed by speaking with a resident caretaker.
You can now change the color of your stabled chocobo's plumage by feeding him snacks.
You can now purchase land for a private estate. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
Subdivisions have been added to all three residential districts. There are now double the amount of plots available for purchase. Travel to the subdivisions is possible via Aethernet shards.
You can now use expansion of duty permits, allowing the dispatchment of retainers on estate property. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
You can now use aetherial wheels. Charge wheels on wheel stands and convert the stored energy into company actions. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.

You can now add a company workshop to your estate. Workshops can be used to craft company projects such as aetherial wheels, housing materials, and airships. Those airships can then be deployed on exploratory voyages. Speak with a resident caretaker for a detailed explanation on the steps required.
A new attraction─the Lord of Verminion─is now available in Chocobo Square!

The following changes have been made to housing: - Estate sharing is now available with private estates. - The brightness of estate lighting can now be adjusted. - Estates not accessed for extended periods of time will be automatically demolished and the plots of land put back up for sale. For further details on these changes, speak with a resident caretaker.

Exploratory missions are now available through the company workshop's voyage control panel. These missions allow you and your company members to explore a remote cluster of islets in the Sea of Clouds known as the Diadem. For further details, speak with the mammet voyager #004A.

Flowerpots and flower vases are now available for placement in all private estates and chambers. Curious crops grown in the flowerpots can be exchanged for materials at residential area material suppliers.
Apartments are now available for purchase in residential areas. Speak with a resident caretaker for details.

The following activities have been added to the Duty Finder and are accessible under Gold Saucer: Triple Triad Battlehall Matches LoVM Player Battles (Non-RP) LoVM Player Battles (RP) LoVM Tournaments Lord of Verminion match registration no longer requires MGP.

The following features have been added to estate orchestrions: Playlists Play All option Repeat option Shuffle option Further information on playlists can be found under the active help topic “The Orchestrion.” Caught fish can now be placed in aquariums and displayed in estates or private rooms.
Paintings are now available for purchase at the Hard Place in Idyllshire. These paintings can be placed in frames and displayed in personal estates, rooms, and apartments.

New exploratory missions are now available through the company workshop's voyage control panel. These missions allow you and your company members to explore a remote cluster of islets in the Sea of Clouds known as the Diadem. For further details, speak with the mammet voyager #004A.

A relocation option is now available to estate owners wishing to move to a new plot of land. In addition, owners will now be granted use of storerooms for the temporary storage of both outdoor and indoor furnishings. Speak with a resident caretaker for details.
Unsure what to wear to the coming seasonal event? Glamour dressers have been added to inn rooms in all of Eorzea's major city–states and Kugane, making gear coordination even easier!
Custom PvP teams can now be formed! View the team creation board located on the Wolves' Den Pier to learn more!

The following temporary restrictions have been placed on future land purchases: ・All new land purchases are limited to free companies. ・Players may only own one private and one free company estate per World per service account. ・Free companies with less than four members cannot purchase land. Plots relinquished by owners will be unavailable for purchase for a limited time.
Message Books can now be found in all estates and apartments. Callers can now leave personalized messages, as well as like the estates.

The following duties have been added to the Duty Finder under “Gold Saucer”: Chocobo Races Chocobo Race: Random Chocobo Race: Sagolii Road Chocobo Race: Costa del Sol Chocobo Race: Tranquil Paths Chocobo Races (Party Member) Chocobo Race: Random Chocobo Race: Sagolii Road Chocobo Race: Costa del Sol Chocobo Race: Tranquil Paths

A new Gold Saucer Active Time Event
“Leap of Faith” is now available!

To coincide with this addition, the GATE
schedule has been updated. Speak with
the Gold Saucer attendant at Entrance
Square for details.

Mannequins are now available for all residences and can be purchased from housing area merchants, estate man/maidservants, hokonin, or housekeeping nodes. Players can use mannequins to display gear, as well as sell it to prospective buyers. Tags can now be attached to all residences and viewed in the following areas: Estate Profile Ward Select Screen Private Chamber Select Screen Apartment Room Select Screen
Achieving a maximum satisfaction level with Zhloe Aliapoh will now allow you to apply glamours to the budding shopkeep.

A new Gold Saucer Active Time Event
“Air Force One” is now available!

To coincide with this addition, the GATE
schedule has been updated. Speak with
the Gold Saucer attendant at Entrance
Square for details.
Nautical maps can now be discovered on certain subaquatic voyages to reveal the whereabouts of additional explorable locations.

A new Gold Saucer Active Time Event
“The Slice Is Right” is now available!

To coincide with this addition, the GATE
schedule has been updated. Speak with
the Gold Saucer attendant at Entrance
Square for details.

A new stage has been added to the Gold
Saucer Active Time Event “Leap of Faith”!

To coincide with this addition, the GATE
schedule has been updated. Speak with
the Gold Saucer attendant at Entrance
Square for details.

You may now try on gear from the Online Store via the Dreamfitting feature.
Access Dreamfitting from the bed in any inn room to try on everything from full outfits to individual pieces, and let your dreams run wild!

When residing in an inn room, you can now choose to cast glamours using items not only from your inventory, but also those stored in glamour dressers or armoires.

Retire to private chambers, and switch up your style in comfort!
